sentences: Marco Benevento (born July 22, 1977) is an American pianist, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, and record producer, who has been a fixture of the New York experimental music rock and jazz scene since 1999.

Marco Benevento (born July 22, 1977) is an American pianist, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, and record producer, who has been a fixture of the New York experimental music rock and jazz scene since 1999.
Benevento was born in Livingston, New Jersey, United States, in 1977.
He graduated from Ramapo High in 1995 and Berklee College of Music in 1999.
He graduated from Ramapo High in 1995 and Berklee College of Music in 1999.

Benevento has been a regular on the New York City contemporary, experimental jazz scene with his involvement in the Jazz Farmers (1999-2001), the Benevento Russo Duo (2002–present) and his own band (2006–present).

The keyboardist currently resides in the Woodstock, NY area with his wife and two daughters.
Benevento's first studio album as a pianist, Invisible Baby, released in 2008, was nominated for Independent Music Awards Jazz Album of the year.

Benevento toured with Ween bassist Dave Dreiwitz and drummer Andrew Borger from 2012 to 2016.
In 2016, Karina Rykman took over on bass for Dave Dreiwitz who had started touring again with Ween.
In 2017 David Butler took over on drums when Andrew started playing with KD Lang and Pink Martini.
In 2009 Benevento began his own record label with manager Kevin Calabro called The Royal Potato Family.
Benevento is one half of the Benevento Russo Duo, an instrumental indie rock, experimental Hammond organ, Wurlitzer electric piano and drum duo that he formed with drummer Joe Russo in 2001.
In 2006, Benevento was featured in Bobby Previte's Coalition of the Willing US and European tour.
In July 2006, Benevento toured with Trey Anastasio, Mike Gordon and Joe Russo.
